Package: coenosr
Title: Reconstruction of the 1991 COENOS Braun-Blanquet Table-Sorting Method
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("K. W.", "Bridges", email = "kim.bridges@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Claude (Anthropic)", role = "aut"))
Description: A faithful reconstruction in R of the methodology embodied in the
    1991 COENOS program, a compiled-Pascal tool for numerical phytosociology in
    the Braun-Blanquet tradition. COENOS sorts a raw species-by-releve table
    into a structured two-way table of differential species groups, using
    inside/outside frequency rules for group formation and reciprocal averaging
    for ordering. The original source is lost; this package recovers the method
    so that what COENOS did can be done again, legibly and verifiably, validated
    against tables the original program produced. This release provides the
    releve-file reader and the species classification (trim) step; group
    formation and ordering follow.
